      <section eId="sec_44_6_87">
        <num>44-6-87</num>
        <content>
          <p>No forfeiture shall result when a tenant for life purports to sell the entire estate in lands. In such a case, the purchaser shall acquire only the interest of the life tenant.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2242; Code 1868, § 2234; Code 1873, § 2260; Code 1882, § 2260; Civil Code 1895, § 3095; Civil Code 1910, § 3671; Code 1933, § 85-609.)</p>
